    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::season_jobs_swallow_root_errors::7bcce77c": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::season_jobs_swallow_root_errors::7bcce77c",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Season aggregation scripts collapse network and parse failures into booleans or \"missing\" states without preserving the original cause.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py",
          "calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py season_exists() catches any Exception and returns False, so a timeout, DNS failure, or JSON bug is indistinguishable from a season that does not exist (lines 32-38).",
          "calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py fetch_game_json_with_retry() catches any Exception and returns (\"missing\", None) after retries, which erases whether the problem was a transport failure, decode failure, or unexpected response shape (lines 69-85).",
          "calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py initially preserves the last exception in fetch_json_with_retry(), but main() then catches Exception around future.result() and retry processing and only appends the game_id to failed_ids, dropping the exception context before reporting (lines 128-153)."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Define one failure model for season jobs: either raise a typed exception with game_id/season context, or return a structured error object that includes category and original message. Keep missing-game cases separate from transient/network/parsing failures.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-06T16:42:13+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-06T16:42:13+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "python",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::same_boundary_different_error_policy::839c6021": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::same_boundary_different_error_policy::839c6021",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 1,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Scripts that all fetch NBA play-by-play data use incompatible error strategies at the same I/O boundary.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py",
          "categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py",
          "step2_build_possessions.py",
          "calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py",
          "calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py, categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py, and step2_build_possessions.py all call requests.get(...), then response.raise_for_status(), and let failures terminate the run immediately (build lines 63-67, categorize lines 66-70, step2 lines 131-136).",
          "By contrast, calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py treats similar request failures as availability probes or missing games and keeps going via False / \"missing\" / {\"status\": \"missing\"} returns (lines 32-38, 41-52, 69-85, 156-164).",
          "calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py uses a third variant: network calls raise from fetch_json_with_retry(), but higher-level orchestration demotes them back into failed_ids bookkeeping (lines 29-39, 128-153)."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Extract a shared fetch layer for NBA play-by-play access with one explicit contract, such as raising domain-specific exceptions (`GameMissing`, `TransientFetchError`, `InvalidPayload`) and letting each script decide only at the top level whether to stop or continue.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-06T16:42:13+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-06T16:42:13+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "python",
      "suppressed": false,
