    },
    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::parse_helpers_silently_hide_bad_values::06315d15": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::parse_helpers_silently_hide_bad_values::06315d15",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 2,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "`parse_int` silently converts any conversion error to `None`, while nearby validation paths raise explicit exceptions.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py",
          "categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Both files define parse_int() with `except Exception: return None` around `int(value)` (build lines 22-28, categorize lines 22-28), so invalid score fields are quietly treated as missing data.",
          "In the same modules, structural validation uses explicit `ValueError` when the game does not resolve to exactly two teams (build lines 78-80, categorize lines 80-82), which means malformed upstream data is sometimes surfaced and sometimes silently ignored.",
